file.content:
components:
  schemas:
    tmp0:
      properties:
        failureReason: {type: string}
        iocBlackListId: {type: string}
        iocType: {type: string}
        iocValue: {type: string}
        success: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp1:
      properties:
        failureReason: {type: string}
        iocBlackListId: {type: string}
        iocType: {type: string}
        iocValue: {type: string}
        success: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp2:
      properties:
        description: {type: string}
        emailDirection: {type: string}
        expiryDate: {type: string}
        iocBlackListId: {type: string}
        iocType: {type: string}
        iocValue: {type: string}
        remediationAction: {type: string}
        status: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp3:
      properties:
        failureReason: {type: string}
        iocBlackListId: {type: string}
        iocType: {type: string}
        iocValue: {type: string}
        success: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp4:
      properties:
        failureReason: {type: string}
        iocBlackListId: {type: string}
        iocType: {type: string}
        iocValue: {type: string}
        success: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp5:
      properties:
        failureReason: {type: string}
        iocBlackListId: {type: string}
        iocType: {type: string}
        iocValue: {type: string}
        success: {type: string}
      type: object
  securitySchemes:
    BasicAuth: {scheme: basic, type: http}
info:
  contact: {email: frikky@shuffler.io, name: '@frikkylikeme', url: 'https://twitter.com/frikkylikeme'}
  description: Automated generation of Symantec Blacklist Ioc
  title: Symantec Blacklist Ioc
  version: 1.0.0
  x-logo: data:image/png;base64,
openapi: 3.0.2
paths:
  tmp0:
    post:
      description: Adds a new IOC via the Upload API
      parameters:
      - description: Add IOCs to which domain; defaults to all domains if left blank
          (global).
        example: swimlane.com
        in: query
        name: Domain
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: ''
        example: Bad subject text
        in: query
        name: Description for IOCs; this description will apply to all being added
          and defaults to 'Swimlane Automation.'
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: 'Options: I, O or B. I=Inbound, O=Outbound, B=Both. Defaults
          to B. will apply to all being added.'
        example: I
        in: query
        name: Email Direction
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: 'Options: B, Q, M, T or H. B=Block and Delete, Q=Quarantine,
          M=Redirect, T=Tag Subject, H=Append header. Defaults to setting found in
          portal. Will apply to all being added.'
        example: B
        in: query
        name: Remediation Action
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: IOC Type; Wildcards * and ? are permitted, use backslash to escape.
        example: spam.pdf
        in: query
        name: Attachment Names
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: IOC Type
        example: swimlane.com
        in: query
        name: Body Sender Domains
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: IOC Type
        example: test.user@swimlane.com
        in: query
        name: Body Sender Emails
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: IOC Type
        example: swimlane.com
        in: query
        name: Body Sender Top Level Domains
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: IOC Type
        example: swimlane.com
        in: query
        name: Envelope Sender Domains
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: IOC Type
        example: test.user@swimlane.com
        in: query
        name: Envelope Sender Emails
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: IOC Type
        example: swimlane.com
        in: query
        name: Envelope Sender Top Level Domains
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: IOC Type
        example: 5a6bdf58-237b-41b6-8ab9-b3a7f190c964
        in: query
        name: MD5 Attachments
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: IOC Type
        example: Swimlane.com
        in: query
        name: Recipient Domains
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: IOC Type
        example: test.user@swimlane.com
        in: query
        name: Recipient Emails
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: IOC Type
        example: 127.60.4.1
        in: query
        name: Sender IP Addresses
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: IOC Type
        example: 192.168.100.0/22
        in: query
        name: Sender IP Ranges
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: IOC Type
        example: 59ce60caf35916de2e456d0f77d5c9a2b5c5c338928b2dcd5883b7f031602768
        in: query
        name: Sha2 AttachmentS
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: IOC Type
        example: String of text
        in: query
        name: Subjects
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: IOC Type
        example: foo.com
        in: query
        name: URLs
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp0'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Symantec Blacklist IOC Add
  tmp1:
    post:
      description: Delete IOC
      parameters:
      - description: IDs which correspond to the list of IOC values given for one
          IOC type.
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: Blacklist IDs
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: IOCs under which domain; defaults to all domains if left blank
          (global).
        example: swimlane.com
        in: query
        name: Domain
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: ''
        example: Bad subject text
        in: query
        name: Description for IOCs; this description will apply to all being added
          and defaults to 'Swimlane Automation.'
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: 'Options: I, O or B. I=Inbound, O=Outbound, B=Both. Defaults

        example: I
        in: query
        name: Email Direction
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: 'Options: B, Q, M, T or H. B=Block and Delete, Q=Quarantine,
          M=Redirect, T=Tag Subject, H=Append header. Defaults to setting found in
          portal. Will apply to all being added.'
        example: B
        in: query
        name: Remediation Action
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: 'The IOC type of the ID(s). The API wants the ID and the correct
          type/value to update. Options: attachmentname, bodysenderdomain, bodysenderemail,
          bodysendertopleveldomain, envelopesenderdomain, envelopesenderemail, envelopesendertopleveldomain,
          md5attachment, recipientdomain, recipientemail, senderipaddress, senderiprange,
          sha2attachment, subject, url'
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: IOC Type
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: The values which correspond to the ID(s) provided. Must have
          a value for each ID.
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: IOC Values
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp1'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Symantec Blacklist IOC Delete
  tmp2:
    post:
      description: 'Return list of IOCs '
      parameters:
      - description: Which domain to get list of IOCs; defaults to all domains (global).
        example: swimlane.com
        in: query
        name: Domain
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp2'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: 'Symantec Blacklist IOC Get List '
  tmp3:
    post:
      description: Upload API to merge or replace IOC
      parameters:
      - description: IOCs under which domain; defaults to all domains if left blank
          (global).
        example: swimlane.com
        in: query
        name: Domain
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: ''
        example: Bad subject text
        in: query
        name: Description for IOCs; this description will apply to all being added
          and defaults to 'Swimlane Automation.'
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: 'Options: I, O or B. I=Inbound, O=Outbound, B=Both. Defaults
          to B. will apply to all being added.'
        example: I
        in: query
        name: Email Direction
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: 'Options: B, Q, M, T or H. B=Block and Delete, Q=Quarantine,
          M=Redirect, T=Tag Subject, H=Append header. Defaults to setting found in
          portal. Will apply to all being added.'
        example: B
        in: query
        name: Remediation Action
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: IOC Type; Wildcards * and ? are permitted, use backslash to escape.
        example: spam.pdf
        in: query
        name: Attachment Names
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: IOC Type
        example: swimlane.com
        in: query
        name: Body Sender Domains
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: IOC Type
        example: test.user@swimlane.com
        in: query
        name: Body Sender Emails
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: IOC Type
        example: swimlane.com
        in: query
        name: Body Sender Top Level Domains
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: IOC Type
        example: swimlane.com
        in: query
        name: Envelope Sender Domains
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: IOC Type
        example: test.user@swimlane.com
        in: query
        name: Envelope Sender Emails
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: IOC Type
        example: swimlane.com
        in: query
        name: Envelope Sender Top Level Domains
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: IOC Type
        example: 5a6bdf58-237b-41b6-8ab9-b3a7f190c964
        in: query
        name: MD5 Attachments
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: IOC Type
        example: Swimlane.com
        in: query
        name: Recipient Domains
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: IOC Type
        example: test.user@swimlane.com
        in: query
        name: Recipient Emails
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: IOC Type
        example: 127.60.4.1
        in: query
        name: Sender IP Addresses
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: IOC Type
        example: 192.168.100.0/22
        in: query
        name: Sender IP Ranges
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: IOC Type
        example: 59ce60caf35916de2e456d0f77d5c9a2b5c5c338928b2dcd5883b7f031602768
        in: query
        name: Sha2 AttachmentS
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: IOC Type
        example: String of text
        in: query
        name: Subjects
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: IOC Type
        example: foo.com
        in: query
        name: URLs
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: 'If True, the task merges. If False, the task replaces. Merge:
          compares IOC Type/Value to database and updates/creates new. Replace: Deletes
          the entire database and replaces with this list.'
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: Merge
        required: true
        schema: {type: boolean}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp3'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Symantec Blacklist IOC Merge or Replace
  tmp4:
    post:
      description: Renew IOC which essentially extends the expiration date
      parameters:
      - description: IDs to renew, renews all if blank. If IDs are provided then IOC
          Type and IOC Values for each ID are required.
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: Blacklist IDs
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: 'The IOC type of the ID(s). The API wants the ID and the correct
          type/value to update. Options: attachmentname, bodysenderdomain, bodysenderemail,

        example: ''
        in: query
        name: IOC Type
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: The values which correspond to the ID(s) provided. Must have

        example: ''
        in: query
        name: IOC Values

      - description: IOCs under which domain; defaults to all domains if left blank

        example: swimlane.com

        name: Domain
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: ''
        example: Bad subject text
        in: query
        name: Description for IOCs; this description will apply to all being added

        required: false

      - description: 'Options: I, O or B. I=Inbound, O=Outbound, B=Both. Defaults

        example: I

      - description: 'Options: B, Q, M, T or H. B=Block and Delete, Q=Quarantine,

        example: B

        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp4'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Symantec Blacklist IOC Renew
  tmp5:
    post:
      description: Update an IOC
      parameters:
      - description: IDs which correspond to the list of IOC values given for one
          IOC type.
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: Blacklist IDs
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: 'The IOC type of the ID(s). The API wants the ID and the correct
          type/value to update. Options: attachmentname, bodysenderdomain, bodysenderemail,

      - description: IOCs under which domain; defaults to all domains if left blank
